[ ITIL 4 Overview ]
- What is ITIL? > A framework designed to manage service organizations 
- Why ITIL 4 exists > Help lead the 4h revolution of technology for mankind
- Value of Service Management
      |   > ITSM Helps all organizations, regardless of their industry or business sector, provide their IT services using the most efficient
      |   > Best practices & efficient operations.
      |   > Service Management is defined as a set of specialized organizational capabilities for enabling value to customers in
      |   > The form of services.
      |   >  Value is perceived and as such is baeed on the recipients perception. Value is subjective.
      |   > Perceived benefits, usefulness, and importance of "something"
      v   
[ Service Value System (SVS) ] > Means of enabling value co-creation by facilitating outcomes that customers want to achieve,
      |   > without the customer having to manage specific costs and risks.
- Guiding Principles
- Governance
-  Opportunity > Service Value Chain > Value

  [Service Valuce Chain ] activities
      |  > 1. Plan
      |  > 2. Improve
      |  > 3. Engage
      |  > 4. Design and Transition
      |  > 5. OBtain and Buid
      |  > 6. Deliver and Support
- Continual Improvement
      |
      | > Warranty: Defined as a the assurance that a product or service will meet agreed requirements.
      |   > When a service is referred to as "fit for use". 
      |   > Warranty is usually concerned with availability, capacity, capability, and security requirements.
      v
[ 7 Guiding Principles ]
- Focus on Value
- Start Where You Are
- Progress Iteratively
- Collaborate & Promote Visibility
- Think & Work Holistically
- Keep It Simple
- Optimize & Automate
